%N A392739 A balanced 4-automatic binary sequence related to Thue-Morse sequence.
%C A392739 The sequence is balanced: a(2n) + a(2n+1) = 1 for all n >= 0. Also a(n) agrees with Thue-Morse A010060(n) on dyadic blocks [2^(2k), 2^(2k+1)-1] and is complemented on blocks [2^(2k+1), 2^(2k+2)-1]. The sequence is 4-automatic with a 3-state DFAO.
%F A392739 a(4n) = a(n), a(4n+1) = 1-a(n), a(4n+2) = a(2n), a(4n+3) = 1-a(2n) with a(0)=0 and a(1)=1.
%F A392739 a(n) = A010060(n) XOR (floor(log_2(n)) mod 2).
%e A392739 For n=5: a(5) = A010060(5) XOR (floor(log_2(5)) mod 2) = 0 XOR 0 = 0.
%t A392739 a[0] = 0; a[1] = 1; a[n_] := a[n] = Which[Mod[n, 4] == 0, a[Quotient[n, 4]], Mod[n, 4] == 1, 1 - a[Quotient[n, 4]], Mod[n, 4] == 2, a[2*Quotient[n, 4]], True, 1 - a[2*Quotient[n, 4]]]; Table[a[n], {n, 0, 79}]
%o A392739 (PARI) a(n) = if(n<2, n, my(q=n\4, r=n%4); if(r==0, a(q), r==1, 1-a(q), r==2, a(2*q), 1-a(2*q)));
